  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThe `BeaconState::get_beacon_proposer_index` function should check that the `slot` argument lies within sensible bounds before attempting to compute a proposer index. Proposer indices are only known for the current epoch and earlier due to the possibility of a validator's effective balance changing upon the next epoch boundary. The lower bound is likely related to the lower bound for the active validator indices (see #922), but could probably be set to the previous epoch for all current uses.\r\n",
